HOUSE BILL NO. HB0021
School finance-routine maintenance worker calculation.
Sponsored by: Select Committee on School Facilities
A BILL
for
1 AN ACT relating to K-12 school finance; eliminating
2 operating expenditures as a factor in the computation of
3 maintenance workers in the routine maintenance and
4 operations component of the education resource block grant
5 model; providing an appropriation; and providing for an
6 effective date.
7
8 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Wyoming:
9
10 Section 1.
11
12 (a) For school year 2025-2026 and each school year
13 thereafter, the education resource block grant model, as
14 defined in W.S. 21-13-101(a)(xiv), shall not include a
15 factor for a school district's operating expenditures when
16 computing the maintenance worker base full-time equivalent
1 HB0021

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0154
1 position resources through the routine maintenance and
2 operations component as contained in paragraph (b)(xxxiii)
3 of "Attachment A" as referenced in W.S. 21-13-101(a)(xvii).
4 Except as specifically provided under subsection (b) of
5 this section, for school year 2025-2026 and each school
6 year thereafter, the maintenance worker resources provided
7 through the routine maintenance and operations component
8 within the education resource block grant model shall be
9 computed in the same manner as school year 2024-2025.
10
11 (b) For school year 2025-2026 and each school year
12 thereafter, the education resource block grant model's
13 maintenance worker base full-time equivalent position
14 resources contained within the routine maintenance and
15 operations component shall be calculated using the average
16 of the following three (3) factors:
17
18 (i) One and one-tenth (1.1) maintenance workers
19 per school building;
20
21 (ii) One (1) maintenance worker multiplied by
22 the total of the allowable gross square footage of
23 education space for the school building in accordance with
2 HB0021

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0154
1 W.S. 21-13-309(m)(v)(G)(II) divided by sixty thousand
2 (60,000), then multiplied by a factor of one and two-tenths
3 (1.2);
4
5 (iii) One (1) maintenance worker multiplied by
6 the total average daily membership for the school building
7 divided by one thousand (1,000), then multiplied by a
8 factor of one and three-tenths (1.3). "Average daily
9 membership" means as defined by W.S. 21-13-101(a)(i).
10
11 Section 2. There is appropriated two million dollars
12 ($2,000,000.00) from the public school foundation program
13 account to the department of education-school finance for
14 routine maintenance payments to school districts made
15 necessary by the amendments enacted in section 1 of this
16 act. This appropriation shall be for the period beginning
17 July 1, 2025 and ending June 30, 2026. This appropriation
18 shall not be transferred or expended for any other purpose
19 and any unexpended, unobligated funds remaining from this
20 appropriation shall revert as provided by law on June 30,
21 2026. It is the intent of the legislature that this
22 appropriation be included in the standard budget for the
